&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;At Coras, we fuse expertise with humanity, rigor with creativity and innovation with curiosity. At the core of our business is the belief that a diversity of perspectives is the key to new thinking. That’s why our team brings together deep industry experience with some of the brightest young minds in Australia. Our values are more than just words on an email signature; we’re driven by an ethos that inspires and governs everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Roles:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have permanent, full-time opportunities at the Consultant and Senior Consultant levels for individuals with strong commercial capability across procurement, contracting and contract management to join our Canberra office. This is a hands-on, service delivery role within our Maritime Sustainment segment, where you will support clients through practical commercial activities across the contract lifecycle, from sourcing and contract development through to contract administration and ongoing management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are open to a diversity of skill levels in this speciality, and while consulting experience would be great, we can help you develop those skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Ideal Candidate:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You have experience working in procurement, contracting and/or contract management roles and are comfortable contributing directly to commercial outcomes. You have experience with Defence contracting and procurement processes, including a working knowledge of the&amp;nbsp;ASDEFCON&amp;nbsp;contracting suite. Experience delivering services to clients such as&amp;nbsp;NSSG,&amp;nbsp;CASG, or other areas within Defence would be highly regarded — if this sounds like you,&amp;nbsp;we’d&amp;nbsp;welcome a conversation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Defence consultancy, we also need you to be an Australian Citizen with the ability to obtain and maintain an AGSVA Security Clearance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Required skills and attributes include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A hands on understanding of key Defence procurement, including the Procurement Policy Framework and Commonwealth Procurement Rules &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to produce clear, accurate commercial documentation and advice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High level&amp;nbsp;of emotional intelligence and humanistic &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great listener, excellent communicator and dedicated &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven&amp;nbsp;track record&amp;nbsp;of delivering quality outcomes  &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Having these other abilities would also be awesome (but not mandatory):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in delivering “Above the Line” consulting / contracting services to Defence and/or the broader Commonwealth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in providing ILS support / management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Defence maritime or&amp;nbsp;other&amp;nbsp;domain sustainment or project experience &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h4&gt;Why join Coras?&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coras prides itself on being a management consultancy with a difference. Underpinned by our core values, we are trailblazers for innovative consulting models and strategic solutions. As a result, we have built a culture that has our people’s aspirations, development and wellbeing front and centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some of our employee benefits include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Well defined pathway for advancement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to SME coaches to support your development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid parental leave provisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to external and internal training, including a consulting skills program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An additional 5 days per year of professional development leave&lt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;At Coras, we fuse expertise with humanity, rigor with creativity and innovation with curiosity. At the core of our business is the belief that a diversity of perspectives is the key to new thinking. That’s why our team brings together deep industry experience with some of the brightest young minds in Australia. Our values are more than just words on an email signature; we’re driven by an ethos that inspires and governs everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Roles:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have opportunities at the Senior Consultant level for individuals with proven engineering skills and experience in the Defence Maritime Industry to join our team in a full-time, permanent capacity. The successful candidate will be Sydney-based and will deliver specialist services to our Maritime Sustainment clients, directly supporting Navy capability&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are open to a diversity of skill levels in this speciality, and while consulting experience would be great, we can help you develop those skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Ideal Candidate:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are experienced in delivering systems engineering services in the Defence Maritime environment. If you have delivered these types of services in, or to, Navy, Naval Shipbuilding and Sustainment Group (NSSG), or other Defence clients in the past, we would love to have a chat.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Defence consultancy, we also need you to be an Australian Citizen with the ability to obtain and maintain an AGSVA Security Clearance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Required skills and attributes include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Bachelor or equivalent level qualification in Engineering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum two years post graduate experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working within the Defence Maritime environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An active NV1 AGSVA Security Clearance (or higher)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work autonomously and solve complex problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective communication skills and proven ability to deliver high-quality written artefacts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High emotional intelligence and strong interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Having these other abilities would also be awesome (but not mandatory):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in delivering “Above the Line” consulting / contracting services to Defence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience applying Systems Engineering principles in the Maritime domain&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with engineering policy / processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in supporting Maritime Sustainment projects / clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in providing ILS support / management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h4&gt;Why join Coras?&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coras prides itself on being a management consultancy with a difference. Underpinned by our core values, we are trailblazers for innovative consulting models and strategic solutions. As a result, we have built a culture that has our people’s aspirations, development and wellbeing front and centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some of our employee benefits include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Well defined pathway for advancement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to SME coaches to support your development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid parental leave provisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to external and internal training, including a consulting skills program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An additional 5 days per year of professional development leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Whole of company annual conference&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work with like-minded people on exciting projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to our Employee Assistance Provider&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;At Coras, we fuse expertise with humanity, rigor with creativity and innovation with curiosity. At the core of our business is the belief that a diversity of perspectives is the key to new thinking. That’s why our team brings together deep industry experience with some of the brightest young minds in Australia. Our values are more than just words on an email signature; we’re driven by an ethos that inspires and governs everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking experienced Defence Maritime Capability Specialists at the Manager and Senior Manager levels to join our growing Maritime Capability team in Canberra.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working alongside Defence and Navy stakeholders, you will support the development, definition and delivery of complex maritime capability outcomes. You will apply your expertise in Defence capability management, maritime operations, project delivery and stakeholder engagement to develop and review the processes, documentation and artefacts required to progress capability outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will operate as a trusted advisor to clients, translating complex operational, technical and strategic information into clear recommendations and decision-ready material. You will help shape capability solutions, support delivery activities, and work across Defence and industry stakeholders to achieve successful outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Ideal Candidate:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are an experienced Defence professional who understands how complex maritime capability is defined, developed and delivered. You bring strong domain knowledge, strategic thinking and the ability to operate confidently across operational, technical and strategic environments. You are comfortable engaging with senior stakeholders, leading delivery activities, and producing high-quality outputs that support Defence decision-making.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will bring:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience in Defence capability management, capability development, capability realisation, or a closely related discipline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of the including how capability decisions progress through the Defence capability lifecycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience developing and reviewing Defence capability artefacts, including briefs, submissions, governance material, requirements documentation, capability plans or related products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to analyse complex information, identify key issues and provide clear, practical advice to senior stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written communication skills, with the ability to create concise and compelling documentation for senior audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience leading projects, workstreams or consulting engagements in complex Defence environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to influence and collaborate across Defence, industry and technical communities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Highly regarded experience includes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting naval capability development, combat systems, engineering, sustainment or acquisition programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with Navy, the Capability Acquisition and Sustainment Group (CASG) or Naval Shipbuilding and Sustainment Group (NSSG), Defence Industry or other Defence organisations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to Defence gate reviews, capability submissions, investment processes or strategic planning activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Qualifications in engineering, project management, Defence studies, strategic studies or related fields&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
